<br>
There are mobs that see invis in hate. I wouldn't call it &quot;lots&quot; though.<br>
<br>
There are two types of routine mobs that see invis: loathing liches and scorn banshees. Note that they see invis - they still can't see through sneak so if you're behing them, you're fine.  <br>
<br>
Scorn Banshees do not roam around the streets. Ever. The only place you'll see them is in the Maestro's house. You may have to maneuver around one or two or wait til they move out of the way to sneak by. <br>
<br>
Loathing liches populate the roamer paths quite a bit so you'll surely see some. There may be a couple in the Maestro's house also. The thing about them is that they have a VERY small agro radius. No lie - I've run right by them or almost ran into them coming around a corner and not gotten agro. If you're lower level or if you linger at all, they will agro to be sure. But it's not as bad as it could be.<br>
<br>
So how hard is it really? That's relative.  <br>
<br>
These days I know hate like the back of my hand. I get ported up and start scouting around checking all the mini bosses. Sure there are see invis mobs, but if you know how things work, you may as well be a shadow. If I needed the book today, I would go up fully dressed and be out in under five minutes.<br>
<br>
If you don't know hate well, it's going to be a lot more tense. And frankly a lot more fun. The risk is the thrill, and it makes the reward all the sweeter. If you want to cut your risk down, duel someone and go up naked with just the evac potion. (Frankly this is the smarter way to do it - even on the best day, wierd things can happen.)<br>
<br>
But it's perfectly do-able and you don't need l33t knowledge or amazing luck. If you succeed, you'll know what it means to be a rogue. And if you failed, it's still worth the trip.<br>
<br>
<br>
